reviews_data.review_text: Awesome environment and service level by
An absolute joy to come here when I am traveling for work. The staff is amazing and Sadie makes the best oat milk chai, too!

I love the vibes of this place, it would be somewhere I could work or study. My sister and I ordered a banana special latte but they were out of bananas. I was a little disappointed, could’ve been a sign to let us know 😅. Also tried to get panini sandwiches but we couldn’t so we got the two breakfast burritos, those were good! The Lady was by herself and it was pretty busy for a weekday, I felt a little bad! She was super friendly tho! Little dusty in some areas, but that was me just trying to find a place to charge my iPad, the outlet was also not working.
Had the Aztec mocha with a bagel while working. Excellent coffee, atmosphere and kind efficient service.
Mollys a great barista always makes me laugh and gives good recommendations! I really enjoyed the monkey business on the summer menu
Wonderful place  & wonderful coffee ☕️
Poorly trained staff or quality control which allows burned items to be served.  It wasn’t worth the money.
Coffee shop looked great. Barista’s energy was different depending upon who came in and it didn’t feel like a welcoming environment for all. Breakfast sandwich was okay.
Such friendly staff everytime. AMAZING coffee. The banana latte they have right now is to die for. Same with the chai latte
The service is always great! Aubrey is super helpful when I didn’t know what to get!!
I was in earlier this week and greeted by Sydney and Aubrey. They are both gems of humans. Super knowledge and fast. The coffee and French toast muffin were amazing!

One of my new hobbies is to visit coffee shops around the Charlotte area. I’ve to this establishment twice and everything has been so yummy thus far. Hot and cold coffees along with the yummy pastries and the service. Def coming back!

Great atmosphere, quality coffee and friendly employees. I appreciated the barista’s suggestion of the “calm bean” which is always my pre-work pick-me-up. Excellent location for studying with soft lights and seating areas near charging outlets.

Aubrey took care of me and it was the best service ever. I love this place.  Thank you.
The Photographer

The atmosphere is bland at Coffee Republic.  I give good grades on coffee, espresso, etc. and the pastries. The patio sits on the parking lot.  Go to Tour de Jour or Rendebrew Coffee in Ballantyne area for a much better choice if you want to sit is a lovely coffee shop atmosphere and relax.
Coffee is always delicious and service is great too
Amazing!! Aubrey was super helpful in finding a drink I would love. Great atmosphere and staff!

It’s not bad, but it’s not great either — just okay. The coffee is slightly above average, which is a plus. However, the food is clearly pre-prepared and simply reheated in a microwave, which takes away from the overall experience.

One major downside is that there’s only one person running the entire place — managing the register, making drinks, preparing food, and handling everything else. It’s understandably overwhelming, and it shows. She isn’t particularly friendly, and you can see from her expression that she’s not happy to be there.

All things considered, it wouldn’t be my go-to coffee shop.

I was visiting Charlotte and went here with some friends! It’s a cute coffee shop with a great atmosphere, good coffee (including seasonals!), and cute area to take photos also. I would definitely stop by here again if I’m in the area

Great coffee it has become our favorite. However, they charge over a dollar for oat or almond milk.i ask you reconsider the amount being charged for plant based options. We are paying $9.80 for a large latte with oat.
I love this coffee and the ambiance is really cool and chill.
Great coffee shop!! The staff were so sweet, it’s dog friendly and my pup and I felt very welcome hanging out on the top floor. Coffee was tasty, with fun flavors available.

I was actually really interested in trying this place out as I frequent a nearby store and had seen it often. I headed there today with my family only to be completely ignored by the barista. We stood there for a good few minutes before heading out. Cool atmosphere though.

I really enjoy the coffee and food. I thought I would give this place a try because of Maddie! She is the best. She always gives great recommendations on foods and drinks are the best! I will definitely keep coming back. ❤️
Great coffee, like the vibe and organic blends available!

Coffee Republic tends to draw me in whenever they have a seasonal drink on the menu.

Last time I came for the Sweetheart and Dragon's Breath.

This time I came for the Midnight Berry and Goo Lagoon.

The only mishap was the Goo Lagoon wasn't sparkling, which is no fault of the barista. It seemed the soda used was from the previous day, so the drink was a bit flat. They were kind enough to remake it!

Overall, the service is great!

Loved the triple chocolate cookie and morning buzz coffee I got today! The coffee shop looked visually stunning and bustling with good vibes. The girl who took my order was really sweet and polite. Thank you for your excellent service and scrumptious treats! I would be happy to come back again sometime!
Stopped by for first time on 4/1 in the afternoon. Super friendly Barista and an amazing caramel latte! Will be back 💯

Great coffee! Highly recommend the Macchiato small and strong how it should be!

Staff are nice and alive.

As Coffee Republic finds their footing it is great to see the improvements each visit.  They have created a chic, inviting and chill environment with the layout and décor.  The menu is vast which invites experimentation, which the baristas stand behind by offering suggestions and re-dos.
I really like their food options and it seems they are getting better at the speed oven.  My first experience was a cold egg sandwich, but ever since it's been steaming.  The Chili Verde wrap is a fun addition that brings some flavor to breakfast.
I think everything is moving in the right direction and this will continue to be in my rotation of morning delights.
Cappuccino was good.
Super friendly staff and delicious breakfast sandwich and coffee. Oh, and the peanut butter cookie! Just get one!

Didn’t realize it was a chain, but should that have mattered? Walked in and felt the chain store vibes. But what was unacceptable was a bare pastry case and empty store at 8am. They were out of the one breakfast sandwich I asked for. I got another and it was a Starbucks-style reheat that was still cold in the middle And when I asked if my coffee could be in a mug they shot that down because their mugs were too small. Coffee tasted decent. Was planning to camp out all morning and work but just wanted to leave. So I did.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Thomas!

We appreciate you taking the time to share your experience. We're sorry to hear that your visit didn’t meet expectations—our goal is to provide a warm and welcoming environment with great coffee and fresh food. Your feedback about the pastry selection, breakfast sandwich, and mug options is really valuable, and we’ll be reviewing it with our team to improve.

If you’d like to discuss your experience further, feel free to reach out to us at daniel@coffeerepub.com. We’d love the chance to make things right. 

We hope to have the opportunity to serve you again in the future!

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: Hi, Each time I have patronized this establishment my drink selection was great. The staff always polite.  Yesterday, 2.14.25 I had the pleasure of meeting a GM. He had patience and help me figure out my order. He was so kind a down to earth.  We spoke briefly about the number of locations the company has. I hate I didn't ask his name. "You know who you are"....lol As a coffee lover, I frequent coffee shops daily, and Coffee Republic is one of my favorite places around. See you soon.... Thank you!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for your kind words, Gee Gee! We truly appreciate your support and are so glad to hear that you've enjoyed your visits with us. It’s great to know our GM made such a positive impression—he’ll definitely know who you’re referring to! Providing excellent service and quality drinks is what we strive for, and it’s always rewarding to hear when we get it right.

We look forward to welcoming you back soon! Next time you're in, be sure to stop by our coffee shop, Coffee Republic, for another great coffee experience. See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Nice place. Good food and good coffee. Pleasant bar, table or upstairs ambiance. Something for all of my moods. 😉
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Kyle! We appreciate your kind words and are glad you enjoyed the food, coffee, and ambiance. Whether you're in the mood for a cozy spot upstairs or a seat at the bar, we’re happy to offer a space that suits every vibe. Next time you're in the area, stop by Coffee Republic in Ballantyne for another great coffee experience. Hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: This is one of my go-to working spots. It’s small and cozy, making it great to focus, and also not too loud (especially the loft area). I’ve also attended events there on topics like self-care, which was incredible.

Thank you, Meghan! We're so glad to hear that Coffee Republic is one of your favorite spots to work. The cozy atmosphere and quiet loft area make it a great place to focus, and it’s wonderful that you’ve also enjoyed our events on self-care. 

We appreciate your support and look forward to welcoming you back soon. See you! Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: I am not a coffee drinker, but their smoothies are incredible! I was with a group of 6 and the service was excellent. Nice intimate atmosphere

Thank you for your kind words, Chris! We’re so glad you enjoyed our smoothies and had a great experience with your group. Providing excellent service and a welcoming atmosphere is what we strive for, and it’s wonderful to hear that it made an impact. 

Next time you’re in Ballantyne, we’d love to have you back at Coffee Republic. See you!

reviews_data.review_text:
I have been there several times & the service has been great & I love the camomile tea with steamed lemonade. The stafff has been very accommodating.

Most recently, I held a self-care workshop in the loft area. It is just the right size for my workshops with the right amount of tables & seating AND privacy!! Looking forward to holding the next one March 25th!

Thank you to the owners, Kalea, for her hospitality & warm personality & allow use to use the space!
Warmly,
Rita 🙃💖
Simple Self-Care by Rita

We can't wait to have you back for your next event on March 25th! See you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best tasting coffees I’ve had in the area. I love the vegan energy balls too! And always the sweetest baristas! The location in Matthews gives cute small town vibes which I’ve missed since moving here!

Thank you so much, Camryn! We're so glad you enjoyed our coffee and vegan energy balls. Our baristas love creating a warm and welcoming experience, and it means a lot to hear that you appreciate them. 

The Matthews location truly has that charming small-town feel, and we're happy it brings a sense of home for you. 

Next time you're in Ballantyne, be sure to stop by Coffee Republic for another great cup—we’d love to see you here!

reviews_data.review_text:
The rise of the Coffee Republic began in the shadow of a once-dominant force: the Tea Kingdom. For centuries, the world had been steeped in tea culture, where a single monarch and an elite class of tea sommeliers dictated the brewing methods and flavors enjoyed by the people. But discontent simmered beneath the surface. The common coffee farmers, tired of the rigid traditions and the overwhelming dominance of tea, sought a new system—one where every coffee drinker had a voice.

In a bold move, the coffee farmers, roasters, and baristas overthrew the last Tea King, spilling his finest Darjeeling and dismantling the monarchy. In its place, they established the Coffee Republic, a system where café owners, bean merchants, and skilled baristas could all participate in the governance of their coffee trade. Instead of a single ruler, power was shared among elected coffee consuls and a council of esteemed roasters, ensuring that no single blend dominated the market.

The early years of the Coffee Republic were filled with struggle. Rival café syndicates often clashed, and there were constant battles over the best brewing techniques. But through perseverance, innovation, and the unwavering belief that coffee was meant to be enjoyed by all, the republic flourished.

Expanding beyond its original cafés, the Coffee Republic pushed into new territories, offering superior roasting methods and advanced espresso technology. Over time, its influence spread, and coffee drinkers from all regions embraced the new order. Though the road was filled with challenges, the rise of the Coffee Republic marked a turning point in history, ensuring that never again would the world be ruled by a single tea-drinking elite. Instead, a new age of rich, bold coffee had begun.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Noah, for this epic review! We're glad you enjoyed the Coffee Republic experience—where every sip is a revolution in flavor. Next time you're in Ballantyne, stop by Coffee Republic for another round of great coffee and treats. See you soon!

Our team takes pride in creating a welcoming atmosphere, and it’s great to know it made a difference. Next time you’re in Ballantyne, why not grab a chai latte from Coffee Republic and stop by again? We’d love to see you!

reviews_data.review_text: I’m really bummed to write a poor review, because I like their coffees and their space, but the wait times have been ridiculous for online orders. I ordered online before my lunch break, and 30 mins later nothing was ready. There were a few customers in person, so I waited until there was no line at all and no one coming in to ask about my food/drink. They checked the order, started making my drink, but told me that the food I ordered was not available. I was on my lunch break, and just got out of two anesthetic procedures. I was so tired and needed to eat. I ended up having to walk somewhere else for food and was late back to work. I really want to like this place, but this experience has been very consistent.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Tess!

We’re really sorry to hear about your experience and completely understand how frustrating it must have been, especially during your lunch break. We truly appreciate your support and your feedback—it’s not the experience we want for our customers. We’re actively working on improving our online order system to ensure faster service and better communication about item availability.

We’d love the chance to make this right. Please reach out to us at daniel@coffeerepub.com so we can follow up directly. We hope you’ll give us another chance to serve you better next time you order at Coffee Republic. 


Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: Very odd interaction today with the shorter white girl with short black curly hair.  I almost thought she was high or something.  She brought me over my drink and I said thank you and then she states again what the drink is which was odd because I already said thank you.  And then she goes to her coworker and said something about why did I bother and something about she only said thank you or didn’t say thank you. I couldn’t quite tell but it was unnecessary and rude.  I wasn’t mean to them so I don’t get it.  She just seemed out of it.  I never had this interaction here before but it was weird.   Normally the workers seem more normal.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Veronica,

Thank you for sharing your experience with us. We’re sorry to hear that your visit didn’t meet the warm and welcoming atmosphere we strive for at Coffee Republic Ballantyne Village. Providing great service is important to us, and we appreciate you bringing this to our attention. 

We’d love the opportunity to make things right—please reach out to us at daniel@coffeerepub.com so we can learn more and ensure a better experience next time. 

We hope to see you again soon for a great cup of coffee! See you!

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: The chai latte is good, the reheated pastries and sandwiches are good, but stop asking for tips when you don’t actually serve the food. Keep in mind, the lowest pre-selected tip amount is 15% and goes up to 25%. Serve the food and it might be worth a tip.
the girl with short curly brown hair is really cute. 😜💘
Every time I'm there it's a wonderful experience! I am so indecisive, but they are patient and give me great recommendations :))) you gotta stop here if you're in the area, you won't regret it!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: I go nowhere else except Coffee Republic for my espresso or matcha drinks anymore and my husband LOVES their black eye drink (same as a red eye but extra espresso). The breakfast sandwiches and cookies are amazing (I haven’t tried the other foods yet but keep eyeing the red velvet muffin!) and we love the atmosphere. Every single barista has been amazing, especially Irina!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks, Sarah!

reviews_data.review_text: Literally my favorite coffee shop. The coffee is amazing, food is delicious, and the people are awesome. Love this place!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're blushing! Thanks so much for taking the time to leave a review!

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely LOVE this coffee shop. They put this new location in Ballantyne Village recently, & it’s right around the corner from me now! Quite literally addictive. I get a PB energy bar almost every day. My recent favorite has been their Ultimate Chai, made with vanilla and cardamom, from their fall menu. I also love their coffee and matcha, & love to get a strawberry cold foam on top!! I’ve honestly never had a bad drink from here! The employees are so kind, warm, & welcoming, & it’s such a cute place to hangout, work on your computer, chat with a friend, or meet someone new!
Ordered through Uber Eats. Everything was cancelled because it was sold out. No communication from them at all. Terrible service. Wanted to support this place but nope. Never again
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Sherrie!

First and foremost, I want to sincerely apologize for the frustration you experienced with your Uber Eats order. It’s completely unacceptable that we failed to communicate with you about the items being sold out, and I can understand why you’re so upset. We truly value your support, and I deeply regret that we let you down this time.

We’re currently working on improving our communication and inventory systems to ensure that situations like this don’t happen again in the future. We want every customer to feel valued and respected, and we clearly missed the mark in this instance.

I would love the opportunity to make it right for you. If you’d like, I’m more than happy to offer a refund for your order, or a credit toward your next visit—whatever you feel would best address your experience. We want to do everything we can to regain your trust and show you that we take your feedback seriously.

Thank you for taking the time to share your thoughts with us. I hope you’ll consider giving us another chance to prove that we can deliver the experience you expect and deserve.

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: I am a big fan of the other Coffee Republic locations but unfortunately in comparison this one just isn't as good. The space is cool for sure. However the service was somewhat rude, the wait was very long, and when I got my drink it was made incorrectly. I was given different milk than what I asked for and was upcharged for it and the flavor I asked for wasn't put in. It's not the worst but I would likely go to other locations before this one.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for your feedback and loyalty. We want you to have the best experience at all locations and would love for you to email us at info@coffeerepub.com. Thanks!

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee. Nice variety of specialty drinks. Service is hit or miss. Some awesome employees and some that seem like I am bothering them coming in, but the coffee is one of the best.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are continuously working to offer the best service, thanks so much for the feedback!

reviews_data.review_text: My coffee drink was absolutely delicious as wall the French toast muffin I had. It was huge! No way could I eat it in one sitting. Prices were reasonable for what you got.
Nice place with a overhead loft with extra seating. Only complaint is that a small block coffee is over $4.  $20 at a place around the corner gets unlimited for a month.
Very nice and personable service.
Good coffe, nice folks. Unique compared to a usual chain. But expensive!

Service was adequate but not great.  Only one person to take and fill orders.    Coffee was not great... weak and little flavor.  I tossed the second half.  Also a little expensive,  especially considering what it is.  Place is noisy and cramped.
Steep prices but not a great set of options or good service
Went here on a weekend day morning. Great ambiance with good seating upstairs. Ambiance was great to sit and get some focused work done

Great place for a coffee and pastry, I love that they also have sandwich and alternative milk options. The staff is friendly and helpful and answered my questions.  I had coffee and a cinnamon twist and my daughter had the iced salty dog latte with a French toast muffin, they were delicious,  we 'll be back!

It has an UPSTAIRS!  The cutest and most customer friendly coffee shop in town, with lots to offer.

The food and the drinks are great.
- Spinache Sausage Feta Quiche is fantastic.
- Their coffees are on point!
- I keep hearing their Chai is awesome.
(EDIT: It is!)

Customer service by Sam and Anna was fantastic. They know their product and can help you make the best choice for your craving needs.

I can't say enough good things about Coffee Republic.

This is a place, you have to experience!
Amazing coffee place with great vibes. Baked items are on point and all the drinks are really great. Staff was so nice!

Great to have a coffee option in Ballantyne Village. The coffee is very good and the food looks delicious (have not had any yet).  The service is great  - always helpful. I wish their menu had the calorie count on the menu - that's the one drawback.  They have a cute interior space (upstairs and downstairs and outside seating).Also, their reward program seems to be very generous and they have pop-up free coffee (ie.when it's raining or cold).  Give them a try.

I'm in town for the week for work, and am staying at the AC Hotel across the parking lot from Coffee Republic, and it caught my eye as somewhere I could pop in to as I come and go. Today I stopped in on my way back to the hotel and I'm quite happy I did. The coffee and the danish I got hit the spot. My only regret is that I didn't notice the shop earlier in the week. Any time I'm in town for work, I now have a trusty place to pop in to, especially if I'm staying at the AC Hotel, because it's super convenient, just a few seconds walk across the parking lot.

Now if only they were bold enough to open a location in Minnesota...
Love the ube latte with matcha a lot!
Clean, friendly staff, excellent quiche- loved my vanilla latte!! Can’t wait to come back!

I really don’t know how to explain this but feel I need to leave a review. Coffee is always pretty good but service well.. Every time I order a food item it seems that people that order about 4-5 behind me get their items before I do and then I have to ask to get my item almost every single time. There’s never a “I’m sorry, have a good day or a thank you” from certain people working there. At this point the personality from the person made me decide not to go back. There really needs to be a better flow or system in place. One of the other customers got so confused cause we didn’t even know who’s food item was who’s so we had to open it up and check. Sadly won’t be returning but hopefully this issue gets better. Service and personality go such a long way!

If I could give this review 12 stars I would! Molly and Samantha do such an amazing job along with the other staff members. Molly and Sam Help me usually when I’m in between clients and come downstairs for a mid afternoon coffee and muffin pick me up! I recommend Their iced salty dog and French toast muffin! You won’t be disappointed!
Coffee republic has become my favorite local coffee shops! I come often and every time I walk in the staff is so welcoming. Molly and Sam are literally the best!

I have had a great experience every time I have visited this location! Everyone is always super nice, especially Molly. She is super attentive, makes suggestions based on your preferences, and always has a smile on her face and cheery disposition. Every drink she has made me so far has been delicious :) Highly recommend this place whenever you need a quick pick-me-up or a bite to eat, their pastries are also very good! Cute place with friendly people and a positive atmosphere.

It’s a very cute spot with a ton of fun drinks and the pasties looked good. Though I did think it was weird that they have food but don’t have a menu online or have a menu in store, when I asked the cashier said we have sandwiches and burritos which doesn’t exactly help. When I asked for a menu she said they used to have a physical one in store but not sure where it was….one physical menu is a little strange for a whole shop. The coffee was decent, probably won’t be going back again.

Coffee Republic has quickly become one of my favorite coffee shops in the Ballantyne area! I have been here on multiple occasions, and every time, without fail, the staff has been welcoming and super friendly! They are more than willing to answer any questions you might have, and make the orders quickly. I enjoy the baked goods they offer, and the atmosphere is inviting and modern. If you are looking to support local shops, then look no further because Coffee Republic is a standout. Compared to some of the other shops around here, the pricing is not terrible, and the service and quality of the food/drinks separates from "your average coffee shop"!

Coffee Republic is a cute coffee shop! their espresso is rich and delicious, and they have so many amazing drink choices. The food is also very good. I love the quiche. Molly is an amazing barista and has great recommendations!

I always want to support local and shop small! However up charging $.1.30 for oat milk is inane! Then, to not receive even a full cup of coffee; for $8.30 is even more insane. When I asked for a full cup of milk but then, didn’t balance it back out with the appropriate about of flavor! It was not worth it and I will not be back!
Molly is amazing!! She truly is the best barista here always helps me with my orders and goes above and beyond with service, she’s great!

$1.20 for an alternative milk. That’s the whole carton at Trader Joes. This place is a rip off. And $1.00 for a flavor?! The syrup in the restaurant bulk grocery store is like $6 for BULK. This is outrageous. NYC isn’t even this expensive.

My wife and I have given this place a try a handful of times. After our first visit, I would have given them 5 stars. The coffee was good and the service was great! Every time we have been in since then has just gone progressively down hill. The coffee is still pretty decent but the wait continues to get longer and longer it seems. They only ever have 1 barista making drinks and 1 other employee taking orders and making food and it’s just too busy for them to keep up with. Several people were waiting on their orders and people were waiting to order. She finally started helping and did not wash her hands. She was not friendly. She didn’t seem like she cared. The service is always great! Aubrey is super helpful when I didn’t know what to get!!

The Photographer

The atmosphere is bland at Coffee Republic.  I give good grades on coffee, espresso, etc. and the pastries. The patio sits on the parking lot.  Go to Tour de Jour or Rendebrew Coffee in Ballantyne area for a much better choice if you want to sit is a lovely coffee shop atmosphere and relax.
Coffee is always delicious and service is great too
Amazing!! Aubrey was super helpful in finding a drink I would love. Great atmosphere and staff!

It’s not bad, but it’s not great either — just okay. The coffee is slightly above average, which is a plus. However, the food is clearly pre-prepared and simply reheated in a microwave, which takes away from the overall experience.

One major downside is that there’s only one person running the entire place — managing the register, making drinks, preparing food, and handling everything else. It’s understandably overwhelming, and it shows. She isn’t particularly friendly, and you can see from her expression that she’s not happy to be there.

All things considered, it wouldn’t be my go-to coffee shop.

I love this coffee and the ambiance is really cool and chill.

Great coffee, like the vibe and organic blends available!

Coffee Republic tends to draw me in whenever they have a seasonal drink on the menu.

Last time I came for the Sweetheart and Dragon's Breath.

This time I came for the Midnight Berry and Goo Lagoon.

The only mishap was the Goo Lagoon wasn't sparkling, which is no fault of the barista. It seemed the soda used was from the previous day, so the drink was a bit flat. They were kind enough to remake it!

Overall, the service is great!

Loved the triple chocolate cookie and morning buzz coffee I got today! The coffee shop looked visually stunning and bustling with good vibes. The girl who took my order was really sweet and polite. Thank you for your excellent service and scrumptious treats! I would be happy to come back again sometime!
Stopped by for first time on 4/1 in the afternoon. Super friendly Barista and an amazing caramel latte! Will be back 💯

Great coffee! Highly recommend the Macchiato small and strong how it should be!

Staff are nice and alive.

As Coffee Republic finds their footing it is great to see the improvements each visit.  They have created a chic, inviting and chill environment with the layout and décor.  The menu is vast which invites experimentation, which the baristas stand behind by offering suggestions and re-dos.
I really like their food options and it seems they are getting better at the speed oven.  My first experience was a cold egg sandwich, but ever since it's been steaming.  The Chili Verde wrap is a fun addition that brings some flavor to breakfast.
I think everything is moving in the right direction and this will continue to be in my rotation of morning delights.
Cappuccino was good.
Super friendly staff and delicious breakfast sandwich and coffee. Oh, and the peanut butter cookie! Just get one!

reviews_data.review_text:
The rise of the Coffee Republic began in the shadow of a once-dominant force: the Tea Kingdom. For centuries, the world had been steeped in tea culture, where a single monarch and an elite class of tea sommeliers dictated the brewing methods and flavors enjoyed by the people. But discontent simmered beneath the surface. The common coffee farmers, tired of the rigid traditions and the overwhelming dominance of tea, sought a new system—one where every coffee drinker had a voice.

In a bold move, the coffee farmers, roasters, and baristas overthrew the last Tea King, spilling his finest Darjeeling and dismantling the monarchy. In its place, they established the Coffee Republic, a system where café owners, bean merchants, and skilled baristas could all participate in the governance of their coffee trade. Instead of a single ruler, power was shared among elected coffee consuls and a council of esteemed roasters, ensuring that no single blend dominated the market.

The early years of the Coffee Republic were filled with struggle. Rival café syndicates often clashed, and there were constant battles over the best brewing techniques. But through perseverance, innovation, and the unwavering belief that coffee was meant to be enjoyed by all, the republic flourished.

Expanding beyond its original cafés, the Coffee Republic pushed into new territories, offering superior roasting methods and advanced espresso technology. Over time, its influence spread, and coffee drinkers from all regions embraced the new order. Though the road was filled with challenges, the rise of the Coffee Republic marked a turning point in history, ensuring that never again would the world be ruled by a single tea-drinking elite. Instead, a new age of rich, bold coffee had begun.

I had coffee and a cinnamon twist and my daughter had the iced salty dog latte with a French toast muffin, they were delicious,  we 'll be back!

It has an UPSTAIRS!  The cutest and most customer friendly coffee shop in town, with lots to offer.

The food and the drinks are great.
- Spinache Sausage Feta Quiche is fantastic.
- Their coffees are on point!
- I keep hearing their Chai is awesome.
(EDIT: It is!)

Customer service by Sam and Anna was fantastic. They know their product and can help you make the best choice for your craving needs.

I can't say enough good things about Coffee Republic.

This is a place, you have to experience!
Amazing coffee place with great vibes. Baked items are on point and all the drinks are really great. Staff was so nice!

Great to have a coffee option in Ballantyne Village. The coffee is very good and the food looks delicious (have not had any yet).  The service is great  - always helpful. I wish their menu had the calorie count on the menu - that's the one drawback.  They have a cute interior space (upstairs and downstairs and outside seating).Also, their reward program seems to be very generous and they have pop-up free coffee (ie.when it's raining or cold).  Give them a try.

I'm in town for the week for work, and am staying at the AC Hotel across the parking lot from Coffee Republic, and it caught my eye as somewhere I could pop in to as I come and go. Today I stopped in on my way back to the hotel and I'm quite happy I did. The coffee and the danish I got hit the spot. My only regret is that I didn't notice the shop earlier in the week. Any time I'm in town for work, I now have a trusty place to pop in to, especially if I'm staying at the AC Hotel, because it's super convenient, just a few seconds walk across the parking lot.

Now if only they were bold enough to open a location in Minnesota...
Love the ube latte with matcha a lot!
Clean, friendly staff, excellent quiche- loved my vanilla latte!! Can’t wait to come back!

I really don’t know how to explain this but feel I need to leave a review. Coffee is always pretty good but service well.. Every time I order a food item it seems that people that order about 4-5 behind me get their items before I do and then I have to ask to get my item almost every single time. There’s never a “I’m sorry, have a good day or a thank you” from certain people working there. At this point the personality from the person made me decide not to go back. There really needs to be a better flow or system in place. One of the other customers got so confused cause we didn’t even know who’s food item was who’s so we had to open it up and check. Sadly won’t be returning but hopefully this issue gets better. Service and personality go such a long way!

If I could give this review 12 stars I would! Molly and Samantha do such an amazing job along with the other staff members. Molly and Sam Help me usually when I’m in between clients and come downstairs for a mid afternoon coffee and muffin pick me up! I recommend Their iced salty dog and French toast muffin! You won’t be disappointed!
Coffee republic has become my favorite local coffee shops! I come often and every time I walk in the staff is so welcoming. Molly and Sam are literally the best!

I have had a great experience every time I have visited this location! Everyone is always super nice, especially Molly. She is super attentive, makes suggestions based on your preferences, and always has a smile on her face and cheery disposition. Every drink she has made me so far has been delicious :) Highly recommend this place whenever you need a quick pick-me-up or a bite to eat, their pastries are also very good! Cute place with friendly people and a positive atmosphere.

It’s a very cute spot with a ton of fun drinks and the pasties looked good. Though I did think it was weird that they have food but don’t have a menu online or have a menu in store, when I asked the cashier said we have sandwiches and burritos which doesn’t exactly help. When I asked for a menu she said they used to have a physical one in store but not sure where it was….one physical menu is a little strange for a whole shop. The coffee was decent, probably won’t be going back again.

Coffee Republic has quickly become one of my favorite coffee shops in the Ballantyne area! I have been here on multiple occasions, and every time, without fail, the staff has been welcoming and super friendly! They are more than willing to answer any questions you might have, and make the orders quickly. I enjoy the baked goods they offer, and the atmosphere is inviting and modern. If you are looking to support local shops, then look no further because Coffee Republic is a standout. Compared to some of the other shops around here, the pricing is not terrible, and the service and quality of the food/drinks separates from "your average coffee shop"!

Coffee Republic is a cute coffee shop! their espresso is rich and delicious, and they have so many amazing drink choices. The food is also very good. I love the quiche. Molly is an amazing barista and has great recommendations!

I always want to support local and shop small! However up charging $.1.30 for oat milk is inane! Then, to not receive even a full cup of coffee; for $8.30 is even more insane. When I asked for a full cup of milk but then, didn’t balance it back out with the appropriate about of flavor! It was not worth it and I will not be back!
Molly is amazing!! She truly is the best barista here always helps me with my orders and goes above and beyond with service, she’s great!

$1.20 for an alternative milk. That’s the whole carton at Trader Joes. This place is a rip off. And $1.00 for a flavor?! The syrup in the restaurant bulk grocery store is like $6 for BULK. This is outrageous. NYC isn’t even this expensive.

My wife and I have given this place a try a handful of times. After our first visit, I would have given them 5 stars. The coffee was good and the service was great! Every time we have been in since then has just gone progressively down hill. The coffee is still pretty decent but the wait continues to get longer and longer it seems. They only ever have 1 barista making drinks and 1 other employee taking orders and making food and it’s just too busy for them to keep up with. There does not seem to be any system in place for mobile ordering, they keep the drinks behind the bar so you have to request your mobile order and thus still wait in line to ask for it and then have an awkward conversation with the employee at the counter when it’s not ready after you ordered it 15 minutes ago. The staff is all very friendly and doing their best but they need more help!
Cute new coffee spot! Enjoyed the vibes. Had the earl grey latte with an extra pump of lavender and vanilla and it was so delicious 😋 looking forward to coming back and bringing a friend
Had some great coffees and tried a French toast muffin. They both where some of the best I've had in a long time.

I recently visited coffee republic with my daughter and had a fantastic experience. They offer a wide variety of coffee choices, each brewed to perfection. The breakfast sandwiches are delicious and well-prepared, making for a perfect morning treat. Prices are quite reasonable, making it a great value for the quality. The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, with good vibes all around. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a great start to their day!
Had a great chai latte!!
Great service and atmosphere! Ghost is very cordial and knowledgeable about coffee. Sophie and the other baristas are always in good spirits. Great place to start your day.
Great service and exceptional coffee.  The espresso blend was so smooth.
We had a lovely family coffee break here. Flat white was tasty and I had ci namın twist,also yummy. Great athmosphere. Will visit a lot💛

I ordered from the coffee republic app. It said it would be ready in 10 minutes. It actually took 40 minutes. Only one person was working. She was friendly. The other employee was taking a lunch break. She was eating right next to us which was unprofessional. When her break ended she walked behind the counter and asked the other employee if she could trade shifts with her next weekend. Several people were waiting on their orders and people were waiting to order. She finally started helping and did not wash her hands. She was not friendly. She didn’t seem like she cared. The quiche was runny. The cinnamon twist was hard, dry, and tasteless. I could not even taste the coffee  in the morning buzz latte. I only tasted milk. I was so disappointed. I won’t be back.
The coffee was okay, but I will try other stuff they have
Such a yummy coffee spot

Found this place when I was looking for a place to study for my boards. Great atmosphere, staff was super friendly! Food and coffee was delicious! So happy I stumbled upon this place! Super cool vibe!
Cute shop, good coffee, good amount of seating (including some chairs outside)

The coffee and muffin was delicious. The prices were reasonable. The atmosphere was very rustic and welcoming. The only thing I didn’t like was the wait. There was only one person making the coffee and it took about 10 minutes. Hopefully they have online ordering soon!
Does not in fact open at 6:30.  Beware fellow early morning commuters!
I really like how they built making it a cozy coffee shop. Welcoming staff and a great coffee. Just need to try other items on the menu. I may become a regular…
energy drinks are soooooo good and the people are so nice.

Best coffee I’ve ever had!!! They make those lattes with loveeee the syrup is never clumpy it’s not too sweet and if you want to switch it up they have energy buzzers instead of coffee!!!!! My favorite is the sweet peach which is seasonal 😊🍑

After placing our order (2 lattes and 2 English muffins) we waited about 15 minutes before we got 1 of the sandwiches. After seeing others who ordered after us receive their drinks (10 minutes) I went back to the cashier to ask for an update on our order. The cashier  pointed behind them and dismissively said "we're working on it." After waiting another 10 minutes my husband walked up to the same cashier and asked for an update. We ended up getting a refund and leaving without the rest of our order. I think it's unfortunate that in 2024, my white husband was given  attention and respect while I, a woman of color, did not receive the same service.
